description: Protect content, SEO, routing, analytics, and privacy contracts in App Router files.
globs: "app/**/*.tsx"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Routes and page composition

- Compose routes from existing components before creating route-local duplicates.
- Preserve approved message hierarchy, CTA intent, factual claims, and public URLs.
- Do not ship placeholder marketing or legal copy.
- Maintain one clear page heading and a logical heading hierarchy.
- Keep metadata, canonical behavior, social sharing, indexation, and structured data aligned with the route brief.
- Track only approved events with stable names and consent-appropriate behavior.
- Changes to `/privacy`, consent disclosures, processors, retention, legal bases, or data rights require Privacy approval.
- Verify the route at mobile and desktop widths and report any visual assumptions.
